#!/usr/local/projects/routing/help/html_filter.pl
When you view a route's record, you will see the following fields (assuming your
account sufficient rights to at least view them):
<ul>
<li><a href="field_Route_Name.cgi">Route name</a>
<li><a href="field_Route_Distributor.cgi">Distributor</a>
<li><a href="field_Route_Driver.cgi">Driver</a>
<li><a href="field_Route_Pickups.cgi">Pickups</a>
<li><a href="field_Route_Source.cgi">Source</a>
</ul>
To modify fields you are allowed to modify, click on
<a href="button_Edit.cgi"><button>Edit</button></a>.  Once you have completed any changes,
click on <a href="button-Update.cgi"><button>Update</button></a>.

<p>Click
<a href="button_Maps.cgi"><button>List maps</button></a>
to view maps of all the times this route has been driven.

<p>Click <a href="button_larr.cgi"><button>&larr;</button></a> to return to a higher menu.

<p>A <a href="search_Patron.cgi">summary</a>
(search) of all the patrons on this route is also shown on this page.  <em>Note</em> that patrons can appear
on multiple routes.

<p>The following pull-downs appear at the end of the patron list for this route:
<ul>
<li><a href="select_Stickers.cgi">Stickers</a> (experimental to create stickers for the bags)
<li><a href="select_Contacts.cgi">Contacts</a> (to download patrons as contacts)
<li><a href="select_Route.cgi">Route</a> (to manage <a href="Route_sheet.cgi">route sheets</a> for the driver)
</ul>


